To determine whether the medium behaves as a conductor or dielectric, we compare the loss tangent \(\tan \delta = \frac{\sigma}{\omega \epsilon}\), where \(\epsilon = \epsilon_0 \epsilon_r\).  
At 100 kHz, \(\tan \delta \approx 900\), which is much greater than 1, so it behaves like a good conductor. At 3000 MHz, \(\tan \delta \approx 0.03\), which is much less than 1, so it behaves like a dielectric.  

